RunInputAssets.Name: ddy
RunInputAssets.Description: A DDY file with design days to be used for the initial sizing calculation.

RunInputAssets.Name: epw
RunInputAssets.Description: EPW weather file to be used for the annual energy simulation.

RunInputAssets.Name: model
RunInputAssets.Description: An energy Model as either a HBJSON, OSM, or IDF.

RunInputAssets.Name: sim-par
RunInputAssets.Description: SimulationParameter JSON that describes the settings for the simulation.

RunInputAssets.Name: units
RunInputAssets.Description: A switch to indicate whether the data in the final EUI file should be in SI (kWh/m2) or IP (kBtu/ft2). Valid values are "si" and "ip".

RunInputAssets.Name: viz-variables
RunInputAssets.Description:
Text for EnergyPlus output variables to be visualized on the geometry in an output view_data HTML report. If unspecified, no view_data report is produced. Each variable should be in "quotes" and should be preceded by a -v option. For example
-v "Zone Air System Sensible Heating Rate" -v "Zone Air System Sensible Cooling Rate".

RunOutputAssets.Name: err
RunOutputAssets.Description: The error report output by the simulation.

RunOutputAssets.Name: eui
RunOutputAssets.Description: A JSON containing energy use intensity information across the total model floor area. Values are either kWh/m2 or kBtu/ft2 depending upon the units input.

RunOutputAssets.Name: html
RunOutputAssets.Description: The result HTML page with summary reports output by the simulation.

RunOutputAssets.Name: result-report
RunOutputAssets.Description: The HTML report with interactive summaries of energy use, HVAC component sizes, and other information.

RunOutputAssets.Name: sql
RunOutputAssets.Description: The result SQL file output by the simulation.

RunOutputAssets.Name: visual-report
RunOutputAssets.Description: The HTML report with hourly EnergyPlus output variables visualized on the geometry.

RunOutputAssets.Name: zsz
RunOutputAssets.Description: The result CSV with the zone loads over the design day output by the simulation.
